# Implementation Plan: PolicyBazaar-Inspired Insurance Platform Frontend

## Overview

Building a comprehensive frontend for an insurance comparison platform similar to PolicyBazaar. The backend is already complete with authentication, products, enquiries, and testimonials APIs. This plan focuses on creating a modern, responsive React frontend with Redux state management and Tailwind CSS styling.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technology Stack Confirmation**
> - Using **Tailwind CSS** as configured in the project (as seen in [tailwind.config.js](file:///c:/Users/USER/Desktop/TestProj/client/tailwind.config.js))
> - Using **Redux Toolkit** for state management
> - Using **React Router DOM** for routing
> - Building **4 initial pages**: Home, About, Learning (Agents), Learning (Customers)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Design Approach**
> The design will follow modern insurance platform aesthetics with:
> - Clean, professional color scheme (blues, whites, greens for trust)
> - Card-based layouts for products and features
> - Responsive design (mobile-first approach)
> - Smooth animations and transitions
> - Clear call-to-action buttons

